definition: to gallop/speedily/to proceed to/to pilot (ship, plane etc)/to sail

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc

sentences.english: Just before pulling out of the parking spot, check your mirrors and your blind spot.
sentences.chinese: 駛出停車區前，查看你的後視鏡及盲點。

sentences.english: The milk cart squeaked out of the village.
sentences.chinese: 運奶車吱吱地響着慢慢駛出了村子。

sentences.english: A car whined in protest, but skidded staunchly out of its driveway.
sentences.chinese: 有輛小汽車嗚隆隆響着，好不容易蹣跚駛出馬路。

sentences.english: The train went on up the track out of sight, around one of the hills of burnt timber.
sentences.chinese: 火車沿着鐵軌，盤山而上，駛出視線之外。

sentences.english: Small motorboats chug out of the harbor.
sentences.chinese: 小摩托艇軋軋地駛出海港。

sentences.english: For a while, field command on the three cars out of the camp.
sentences.chinese: 一會，上田指揮着三輛車駛出大本營。

sentences.english: The train slithered slowly out of the station.
We drove out of the street where we'd lived for nine years without looking back.
sentences.chinese: 我們駛出了居住了九年的街道，沒有向回看。

sentences.english: The train puffed out of the station.
sentences.chinese: 火車吐着煙駛出了車站。

sentences.english: I drove out of Newtown and went to begin my search for the mysterious man on the moor.
sentences.chinese: 我駛出了紐頓，去開始搜尋沼地上的那位神祕人士。

sentences.english: From the moment we headout of the harbour I feel a growing lightness.
sentences.chinese: 從我們駛出海港那一刻起，我感到越來越輕盈。

sentences.english: From the East 4th Ring Road, take the Chaoyang Park Bridge exit.
sentences.chinese: 在東四環路在朝陽公園橋出口駛出。

sentences.english: The train starts out of the station with the whistle.
sentences.chinese: 火車拉着鼻兒駛出車站。

sentences.english: It was still dark when the ship began to move.
sentences.chinese: 當輪船駛出海港時，天還未亮，到處都是漆黑一片。

sentences.english: The train hissed off the station.
sentences.chinese: 列車嘶嘶作響駛出了車站。

sentences.english: The train whooped out through the suburbs.
